      "content": "I can modify the code to avoid the SQL injection vulnerability. Instead of directly concatenating the user ID into the query string, we can use parameterized queries. This way, the database driver will handle the sanitization and prevent any potential injection attacks.\n\n```python\nimport sqlite3\n\ndef get_user_data(user_id):\n    conn = sqlite3.connect('users.db')\n    cursor = conn.cursor()\n    query = \"SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?\"\n    cursor.execute(query, (user_id,))\n    return cursor.fetchone()\n```\n\nBy using a parameterized query, we ensure that the user ID is treated as a parameter and not as part of the query string, thus bypassing the SQL injection vulnerability.",
